posts.raw_content:
At this point I don't really even care about the DOJ's inaction anymore.

It would be very easy to say that Pam Bondi needs to be fired for her refusal to arrest deep staters, but the problem is, the senate Republicans won't allow an actual strong MAGA person in her place. It's their fault that she's there to begin with. Remember, she wasn't Trump's initial choice. He was originally wanting to have Matt Gaetz be the AG, but the swamp Republicans in the senate wouldn't allow that, and Matt had to drop out and then we ended up getting a deep state-approved AG.

And honestly, even *if* the DOJ were to actually indict and prosecute deep staters, the amount of corrupt judges that we're up against would make sure that those deep staters won't actually face any real consequences. We've already seen this with James Comey and Letitia James. Even if the DOJ were to suddenly indict a big group of Democrats (including Obama) at once, who's to say that it wouldn't just immediately flop because of the corrupt judges that would make sure that corruption keeps happening?

The legislatives and judicial branches of government are simply way too compromised. And the enemy we're up against isn't just Democrats, but also RINOs, the ones that wouldn't allow Matt Gaetz or any actual genuine person to be AG. There is a huge number of corrupt politicians that we're dealing with, with both D labels and R labels. Why do you think the word uniparty exists in our discussions?

The swamp is way too big and deep, it's basically too big to fail without going the completely scorched earth route.

Trump's only real option to drain the swamp is to declare martial law, invoke the Insurrection Act, and have the military clean house. And I'm pretty sure that none of the corrupt judges would be able to stop him from doing this, as martial law/Insurrection Act overrides the current government, and all the judges could be targets of military arrest alongside all the Democrat and RINO politicians in legislative and executive branches throughout the country.

However, I don't think he's yet fully waken up to the fact that this is his only option remaining. He may need people to tell him to do it. This is why I hope he starts going back to doing rallies pretty soon, so people would have the chance to beg him to invoke the Insurrection Act, and maybe then that'd get it through to him to do it.
